{"nodes": [{"id": "draft6_0_src_phase8_exp1_experiment_1", "label": "P8.1 \u2014 the gate bake-off", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "draft6.0/src/phase8/exp1/experiment-1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_phase8_exp1_experiment_1_ddm_gate", "label": "DDM \u2014 the committed awake gate", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0/src/phase8/exp1/experiment-1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Two-threshold error detector chosen as the committed awake gate: holds accuracy-held at the oracle level (0.448) with FAR 0.000 on the nuisance segment at the lowest defensible fire-fraction (f=0.003); ADWIN ties it, absolute-theta is struck for false-firing, and the learned budget-gate is spine-flagged."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_phase8_exp1_experiment_1_absolute_theta_struck", "label": "absolute-\u03b8 gate \u2014 struck (false-fires on nuisance)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0/src/phase8/exp1/experiment-1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A fixed-loss-threshold gate that holds accuracy but false-fires on the nuisance covariate shift (FAR 0.042, above the stationary floor) even though no class changed \u2014 a magnitude leak matching the spine's warning; struck as held-not-clean."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_phase8_exp1_experiment_1_adwin_gate", "label": "ADWIN \u2014 ties DDM as committed-eligible", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "draft6.0/src/phase8/exp1/experiment-1.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Two-window adaptive error detector; ties DDM at FAR 0.000, f=0.003, committed-eligible, but DDM is chosen as the standard reference detector."}, {"id": "draft6_0_src_phase8_exp1_experim